      .content.info
        h2 What you'll need
        p Students will need a 90-day visa to account for the 12-week course. They will also need to book their own flights to and from Amsterdam. Students are expected to find a suitable housing option for the duration of their stay. NYCDA will provide a list of possible housing options upon request. Students must have up-to-date vaccinations before leaving for Amsterdam.
        p A Mac or PC laptop. We'll help you get it set up with all of the software required.
        p The motivation and drive to complete an intense, full-time curriculum.
    .content-area.brand
      .content.info
        h2 Financing
        p Courses at The New York Code + Design Academy are primarily financed in one of two ways:

        p <strong>Students may set up a payment plan with NYCDA without taking out a loan or paying interest</strong>. Tuition is divided into installments, with the balance due before the end of class.
        p Students may apply for a loan with one of our financing partners. ClimbCredit, Affirm, Pave, and Skills Fund can offer students a customized payment plan in monthly installments (This option is only available to U.S. students).
        p Other financing partners and plans are available. If you have any questions, please contact <strong>info@nycda.com</strong>.
        
        p: em We believe that everyone should have the opportunity to learn to code, and NYCDA offers a variety of finance options for prospective students.

        p Ready to start coding?
        a(href="#"): strong Fill out an application now.
    .content-area.white
      .content.info
        h2 Transportation

        p There are two main modes of widely used transportation in Amsterdam: public transportation and cycling. Both offer their own distinct advantages and both are simple and easy to use.

        h4 Public Transportation

        p Amsterdam utilizes the public transport chip card (OV-chipkaart) for travel on trams, buses, and metros. GVB day passes provide unlimited travel on the GVB network in Amsterdam (GVB buses, metros, and trams) for a set period of time (1-7 days). Seven day passes will provide the most use and are priced at 32 Euros.

        h4 Cycling

        p Biking provides a healthy, practical, and enjoyable mode of transportation. Amsterdam is extremely bike-friendly with a network of cycle routes and flat landscape. There are bike rentals all over, and for the purpose of safety, many establishments offer brightly-colored bikes to alert pedestrians.
    .content-area.brand
      .content.info
        h2 Weather

        p Weather in Amsterdam is cool and brisk throughout the year. August is the hottest month in Amsterdam, with an average temperature of 17°C (63°F), and the coldest is January, at 3°C (37°F), with the most daily sunshine hours at 11 in June. The wettest month is November, with an average of 90mm of rain. Expect average temperatures of 10°C (50°F) throughout your stay.
    .content-area.white
      .content.info
        h2 Safety

        p Amsterdam is one of the top 25 safest cities in the world, with a much lower crime rate than many other popular European capitals. In large parts of the city, there are always at least a few people out and about, no matter whether it's Saturday night or Wednesday 3am in the morning.
        p Students should be advised of dangers such as:
        ul
          li Pickpockets
          li Bag/Phone snatchers
          li Getting hit by bikes
          li Getting hit by trams
          li Drugs and alcohol
